\ see-tree expands each colon-word call inline (indented two spaces),
\ recursively, down to primitives; recursive calls print as `name ...`.

: leaf | a b | a b f* a b f+ ;
: mid  | x | x x leaf ;
' mid see-tree

\ recursion is guarded: a self-call prints as a leaf, no infinite expansion
: rec | n | n 1.0 f- rec ;
' rec see-tree

\ non-colon target reports itself
variable V
' V see-tree
